{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> βᾰσῐλ-εύω</b>, <br /> <b>to be king, rule, reign,</b> οὐ μέν πως πάντες βασιλεύσομεν ἐνθάδ᾽ Ἀχαιοί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.203; ἶσον ἐμοὶ βασίλευε 9.616 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν ὑμῖν.. βασίλευε <b>was king</b> among you, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.47; ὄφρ᾽ Ἰθάκης κατὰ δῆμον.. βασιλεύοι 22.52 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also of a woman, ἢ βασίλευεν ὑπὸ Πλάκῳ <b>reigned as queen,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.425; ἡ δὲ Πύλου βασίλευε 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.285 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: in <i>aorist</i>, <b>to have become king,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>genitive</i>, <b>to be king of, rule over,</b> ἐν.. Ἰθάκῃ βασιλεύσει Ἀχαιῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.401, etc.; βασιλεύοντος βασιλέων Ἀρσάκου “PAvrom.” 1 A 1\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>dative</i>, <b>to be king among,</b> Γιγάντεσσιν βασίλευεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 7.59; later β. ἐπὶ τὰς δύο βασιλείας LXX.1Mac.1.16 \">LXX+8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be governed by a king,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 576d, 576e, +others, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1284b39, etc.: c._accusative_ _cognate_, βασιλείαν πασῶν δικαιοτάτην βασιλεύεσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 680e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>to be governed</b> or <b>administered,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.106, etc.; ὑπὸ νόμου 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 2.19 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: hence, <b>submit to the king,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Sulla” 12. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> <b>to be</b> ἄρχων β. at Athens, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 18.5, “IG” 12.776, +others;\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] of other magistrates, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 709 (from Chersonesus), 1054 (from Samothrace). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__c</b></Level4> later ἡ βασιλεύουσα πόλις the <b>imperial</b> city, of Rome, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 3.98c, compare “CPHerm.” 125ii3. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>enjoy as master,</b> τῶ χρυσῶ β. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 21.60 codices \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>live royally,</b> β. ἐν πενίᾳ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.101d, cf. NT.1Cor.4.8. \">NT+1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> causal, <b>appoint as king,</b> τινά [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Josh.9.6 \">LXX</a>]; but β. τισὶ βασιλέα <b>make</b> them <b>a king,</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"LXX.1Ki.8.22, 12.1. \">LXX</a>]","strongNumber":"G0936","accentedUnicode":"βασιλεύω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0932","matchingForm":"βασιλεία","stepTransliteration":"basileia","gloss":"kingdom","_zh_tw_Gloss":"國","_es_Gloss":"reino","_zh_Gloss":"国"},{"strongNumber":"G0933","matchingForm":"βασίλειον","stepTransliteration":"basileion","gloss":"palace","_zh_tw_Gloss":"王宮","_es_Gloss":"palacio","_zh_Gloss":"王宫"},{"strongNumber":"G0934","matchingForm":"βασίλειος","stepTransliteration":"basileios","gloss":"kingly","_zh_tw_Gloss":"君尊","_es_Gloss":"real","_zh_Gloss":"君尊"},{"strongNumber":"G0935","matchingForm":"βασιλεύς","stepTransliteration":"basileus","gloss":"king","_zh_tw_Gloss":"王","_es_Gloss":"rey","_zh_Gloss":"王"},{"strongNumber":"G0937","matchingForm":"βασιλικός","stepTransliteration":"basilikos","gloss":"royal","_zh_tw_Gloss":"大臣, 王","_es_Gloss":"real","_zh_Gloss":"大臣, 王"},{"strongNumber":"G0938G","matchingForm":"βασίλισσα","stepTransliteration":"basilissa","gloss":"queen","_zh_tw_Gloss":"女王","_es_Gloss":"reinar","_zh_Gloss":"女王"},{"strongNumber":"G4821","matchingForm":"συμβασιλεύω","stepTransliteration":"sumbasileuō","gloss":"to reign with","_zh_tw_Gloss":"一同作王","_es_Gloss":"reinar con","_zh_Gloss":"一同作王"}],"shortDef":"to reign as a king, become king","mediumDef":"to reign as a king, become king <br /><b>to possess regal authority, be a king, reign; to rule, govern,</b> <ref='Mat.2.22'>Mt. 2:22</ref>; <i>metaphorically</i> <b>to be in force, predominate, prevail,</b> <ref='Rom.5.14, 17, 21'>Rom. 5:14, 17, 21</ref>; <i>metaphorically</i> <b>to be in kingly case, fare royally,</b> <ref='1Co.4.8'>1Cor. 4:8</ref>","stepGloss":"to reign","stepTransliteration":"basileuō","count":21,"_es_Definition":"gobernar, reinar ; volverse como un rey (1CO.4:8)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 作王, 統治<br>2) 成為王 (得到皇室權力)","_zh_Definition":"1) 作王, 统治<br>2) 成为王 (得到皇室权力)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"thống trị; trị vì","_zh_tw_Gloss":"作王","_es_Gloss":"reinar","_zh_Gloss":"作王"}]}